tlog_lib CHANGELOG
==================

- 2.0.2 | Mar 02 2026:
  [New] CLI version cross-check: standalone tlog warns on stderr when
      TLOG_VERSION and TLOG_LIB_VERSION diverge after sourcing the library;
      catches mismatched extraction or partial upgrade (F-050)
  [New] _tlog_check_baserun_perms() advisory helper: warns on stderr when
      baserun directory is world-writable; non-fatal (always returns 0);
      called from tlog_read(), tlog_journal_read(), tlog_advance_cursors()
      (F-019)
  [New] tlog_journal_read() flock support: optional cursor locking via
      TLOG_FLOCK=1; returns exit 4 on lock contention; same pattern as
      tlog_read() (F-008)
  [New] CLI /tmp warning: when running as root with BASERUN=/tmp, emits
      advisory warning directing user to set -b/--baserun or BASERUN env;
      gated on cursor-using commands only (--full excluded); complements
      library-level world-writable detection (F-033)
  [Change] Extract _tlog_handle_rotation() helper: compressed files
      decompressed once to temp file (was twice); reuses existing helpers;
      consolidates rotation block in tlog_read() (F-021, F-022, F-026)
  [Fix] _tlog_handle_rotation() pipe fallback: when mktemp fails or
      decompression write fails (low disk, quota, corrupt archive), fall back
      to pipe-based decompression instead of silently dropping rotated content;
      preserves data under degraded conditions
  [Change] Remove CLI _tlog_validate_name() override: CLI now delegates to
      the library function (return 1) with || exit 1 at call sites; eliminates
      function collision where the CLI redefined a library internal
  [Change] Extract _tlog_journal_get_cursor() helper: centralizes journal
      cursor capture pipeline used at 3 call sites (F-024)
  [Change] Hoist numeric validation regex to library-scope _TLOG_NUMERIC_PAT;
      eliminates 5 identical local declarations (F-025)
  [Change] _tlog_get_size() bytes branch delegates to tlog_get_file_size();
      removes duplicated stat/wc -c logic (F-027)
  [Change] _tlog_write_cursor() case statement: add explicit bytes) branch
      and invalid-mode error path (was silently handled by wildcard); all 12
      existing call sites safe — defense-in-depth only (F-020)
  [Change] _tlog_write_cursor() emits stderr warning on mktemp or rename
      failure; previously failed silently at all 12 call sites (F-007)
  [Change] _tlog_parse_cursor() header comment documents out-parameters
      (_tlog_cursor_value, _tlog_cursor_mode) and return codes (F-023)
  [Change] CLI --first-run flag validates value (must be 'skip' or 'full');
      rejects typos with actionable error message, consistent with --mode
      validation (F-011)
  [Change] Test version assertions use dynamic EXPECTED_VERSION from sourced
      library instead of hardcoded strings; version bumps no longer require
      test edits (F-049)
  [Change] Source guard test now verifies journal registry survives
      re-sourcing instead of checking a static version string (F-042)
  [Change] CI test matrix now requires lint job to pass before running tests;
      prevents wasted CI minutes on syntactically invalid code (F-046)
  [Change] Remove 4 duplicate BATS tests from suite (133 to 129 before
      2.0.2 additions) (F-032)
  [Fix] Baserun directory validated before processing in tlog_read(),
      tlog_journal_read(), and tlog_advance_cursors(); prevents journal
      attempt or cursor operations on missing baserun (F-010)
  [Fix] Validate SCAN_MAX_LINES, SCAN_TIMEOUT, and max_lines arguments in
      tlog_read_full() and tlog_journal_read_full(); non-numeric values
      default to 0 with stderr warning (F-002)
  [Fix] --status subcommand: correctly display corrupt cursor state instead
      of showing "not initialized"; show raw cursor content for diagnosis
      (F-037)
  [Fix] --status long help: add exit code note — exits 0 even for corrupt
      or uninitialized cursors (F-034)
  [Fix] --reset subcommand: add JTS orphan temp file cleanup glob
      (.NAME.jts.XXXXXX) alongside existing cursor temp file glob; prevents
      orphaned journal timestamp temp files from accumulating (F-051)
  [Fix] CI lint step: add bash -n syntax checking and include
      tests/run-tests.sh in shellcheck scope (F-044, F-045)
  [Fix] README: add return codes for tlog_journal_read (0, 1, 3, 4) and
      tlog_journal_read_full (0, 1, 3) (F-052)
  [New] BATS tests: 67 new tests (196 total) covering arithmetic validation,
      cursor write failures, journal flock and stale protection, baserun
      validation, world-writable and CLI /tmp warnings, version cross-check,
      security checks, rotation refactoring, and remaining audit gaps

- 2.0.1 | Mar 01 2026:
  [Fix] Library-level tlog_name path traversal validation in tlog_read,
      tlog_adjust_cursor, tlog_journal_read, tlog_journal_read_full, and
      tlog_advance_cursors -- reject names containing '/' or equal to '.'/'..';
      defense-in-depth alongside existing CLI validation (C-002)
  [Fix] Journal cursor content validation: allowlist format check before
      interpolation into --after-cursor argument; rejects shell metacharacters,
      clears corrupt cursor to trigger timestamp fallback (C-003/F-014)
  [Fix] Journal timestamp content validation: numeric-only check before
      interpolation into --since=@ argument; clears corrupt value to trigger
      first-run fallback (C-003/F-015)
  [Change] Document intentional $jfilter unquoted expansion at all 8 SC2086
      shellcheck directive sites with explanatory comments (F-016)
  [New] BATS tests: 18 new tests for library-level name validation (positive,
      false-positive, and security tests) and journal content validation
      (cursor/timestamp format checks, corrupt data handling)
  [Fix] tlog_advance_cursors: pass per-service journal filter to journalctl
      --show-cursor instead of capturing global cursor position
  [Fix] tlog_advance_cursors: validate TLOG_MODE before processing (matches
      tlog_read pattern)
  [Change] tlog_advance_cursors: hoist journalctl availability check outside
      loop for efficiency
  [New] BATS tests for tlog_advance_cursors journal branch (7 tests)

- 2.0.1 | Feb 27 2026:
  [Fix] Align Dockerfile files/ COPY path with test path: /opt/tlog_lib/files/
      to /opt/files/ — test helper resolves PROJECT_ROOT from BATS_TEST_DIRNAME
      parent, so files/ must be a sibling of tests/ under /opt
  [Change] Standardize container test path from /opt/tlog_lib/tests to
      /opt/tests — aligns with batsman default, eliminates need for
      test-path CI override
  [New] tlog_lib.sh: shared Bash library for incremental log file reading
      with cursor-based position tracking; multi-mode tracking (byte-offset
      via tail -c, line-count via tail -n) selectable per call or TLOG_MODE
      env; mode-aware cursor format (bare number = bytes, L:N = lines) with
      automatic mismatch detection and reset; configurable first-run behavior
      (TLOG_FIRST_RUN=skip|full); structured error codes 0-4; source guard
      prevents double-sourcing
  [New] Atomic cursor writes via mktemp + mv -f; optional flock-based
      cursor locking (TLOG_FLOCK=1) with 5-second timeout; cursor validation
      with regex check and auto-reset on corruption; stale cursor protection
      via mtime touch on every tlog_read call
  [New] Rotation-aware delta reads: .1 and compressed variants (.1.gz,
      .1.xz, .1.bz2, .1.zst, .1.lz4) with runtime tool availability check
      via command -v; uncompressed .1 retains highest priority; compressed
      files read via pipe (never decompressed on disk); generic decompression
      dispatch via _tlog_is_compressed() and _tlog_cat_file(); supports both
      create and copytruncate logrotate strategies
  [New] tlog_adjust_cursor(): mode-aware cursor subtraction for in-place
      log trim with clamp-to-zero; tlog_advance_cursors(): fast-forward
      multiple file and journal cursors from FILE|TAG pairs
  [New] Journal support: registry-based filter system via parallel indexed
      arrays (avoids declare -A scope issues); tlog_journal_register() for
      consuming projects to define service-to-journalctl mappings;
      tlog_journal_read() cursor-based with timestamp fallback;
      tlog_journal_read_full() for scan mode with timeout support
  [New] Standalone tlog CLI wrapper: sources tlog_lib.sh with security
      check (root ownership, not world-writable); option parsing (-m/--mode,
      -b/--baserun, -f/--flock, --first-run); subcommands (--full, --status,
      --reset, --adjust); version banner (-v/--version), short help (-h),
      detailed help with examples (--help); full backward compatibility with
      positional interface (file, tlog_name, optional mode) preserved;
      BASERUN sed-replaced at install time for cursor storage security
  [New] --status subcommand: display cursor state (path, mode, value, age),
      optional file argument shows size and pending delta, reports .jts and
      .lock presence; read-only — does not modify any files
  [New] --reset subcommand: delete cursor, .jts, .lock, and orphaned temp
      files; reports each deletion; always exits 0
  [New] --adjust subcommand: delegates to tlog_adjust_cursor() for mode-aware
      cursor subtraction after in-place log trimming
  [New] --full subcommand: delegates to tlog_read_full() for cursorless
      full-file reads; does not require BASERUN
  [New] BATS test suite: 133 tests covering both tracking modes, rotation
      (including copytruncate and multi-format compression), cursor validation,
      flock locking, atomic writes, journal functions, and standalone CLI
      (58 tests covering option parsing, subcommands, help/version,
      false-positive verification, path traversal rejection, and mode
      validation); Docker infrastructure via batsman shared framework with
      9 OS targets; GitHub Actions CI via batsman reusable workflow
  [New] README.md: public-facing documentation with platform support matrix,
      API reference, security guidance for cursor storage, and usage examples
  [Fix] Cursor name path traversal: reject names containing '/' or equal
      to '.'/'..'; prevents --reset, --status, --adjust, and read from
      operating on files outside the BASERUN directory
  [Fix] Tracking mode validation: tlog_read() and standalone CLI wrapper
      reject invalid mode strings (e.g., 'line' instead of 'lines') before
      any I/O; prevents silent cursor mismatch reset loop on typos;
      defense-in-depth across library and CLI layers
  [Fix] Shellcheck CI: replace incorrect source= directive with
      disable=SC1090,SC1091 for dynamic library source path; resolves lint job
      exit 1 on all CI runs
  [Fix] CentOS 7 journal test: use nonexistent PATH instead of /usr/bin:/bin
      to reliably hide journalctl on systemd systems; avoids POSIX empty-PATH
      CWD-search edge case
